54   const config = __webpack_require__(93036);
55   const nativeExec = __webpack_require__(55460);
56   const regexp_tree_1 = __webpack_require__(3661);
57   const weakMeasurementRegExp = new WeakMap();
58   function exec(string) {
59       return config.mode === "spec-compliant"
60           ? execSpecCompliant(this, string)
61           : execLazy(this, string);
62   }
63   function execLazy(regexp, string) {
64       const index = regexp.lastIndex;
65       const result = nativeExec.call(regexp, string);
66       if (result === null)
67           return null;
68       // For performance reasons, we defer computing the indices until later. This isn't spec compliant,
69       // but once we compute the indices we convert the result to a data-property.
70       let indicesArray;
71       Object.defineProperty(result, "indices", {
72           enumerable: true,
73           configurable: true,
74           get() {
75               if (indicesArray === undefined) {
76                   const { measurementRegExp, groupInfos } = getMeasurementRegExp(regexp);
77                   measurementRegExp.lastIndex = index;
78                   const measuredResult = nativeExec.call(measurementRegExp, string);
79                   if (measuredResult === null)
80                       throw new TypeError();
81                   makeDataProperty(result, "indices", indicesArray = makeIndicesArray(measuredResult, groupInfos));
82               }
83               return indicesArray;
84           },
85           set(value) {
86               makeDataProperty(result, "indices", value);
87           }
88       });
89       return result;
90   }
91   function execSpecCompliant(regexp, string) {
92       const { measurementRegExp, groupInfos } = getMeasurementRegExp(regexp);
93       measurementRegExp.lastIndex = regexp.lastIndex;
94       const measuredResult = nativeExec.call(measurementRegExp, string);
95       if (measuredResult === null)
96           return null;
97       regexp.lastIndex = measurementRegExp.lastIndex;
98       const result = [];
99       makeDataProperty(result, 0, measuredResult[0]);
100      for (const groupInfo of groupInfos) {
101          makeDataProperty(result, groupInfo.oldGroupNumber, measuredResult[groupInfo.newGroupNumber]);
102      }
103      makeDataProperty(result, "index", measuredResult.index);
104      makeDataProperty(result, "input", measuredResult.input);
105      makeDataProperty(result, "groups", measuredResult.groups);
106      makeDataProperty(result, "indices", makeIndicesArray(measuredResult, groupInfos));
107      return result;
108  }
109  function getMeasurementRegExp(regexp) {
110      let transformed = weakMeasurementRegExp.get(regexp);
111      if (!transformed) {
112          transformed = transformMeasurementGroups(regexp_tree_1.parse(`/${regexp.source}/${regexp.flags}`));
113          weakMeasurementRegExp.set(regexp, transformed);
114      }
115      const groupInfos = transformed.getExtra();
116      const measurementRegExp = transformed.toRegExp();
117      return { measurementRegExp, groupInfos };
118  }
119  function makeIndicesArray(measuredResult, groupInfos) {
120      const matchStart = measuredResult.index;
121      const matchEnd = matchStart + measuredResult[0].length;
122      const hasGroups = !!measuredResult.groups;
123      const indicesArray = [];
124      const groups = hasGroups ? Object.create(null) : undefined;
125      makeDataProperty(indicesArray, 0, [matchStart, matchEnd]);
126      for (const groupInfo of groupInfos) {
127          let indices;
128          if (measuredResult[groupInfo.newGroupNumber] !== undefined) {
129              let startIndex = matchStart;
130              if (groupInfo.measurementGroups) {
131                  for (const measurementGroup of groupInfo.measurementGroups) {
132                      startIndex += measuredResult[measurementGroup].length;
133                  }
134              }
135              const endIndex = startIndex + measuredResult[groupInfo.newGroupNumber].length;
136              indices = [startIndex, endIndex];
137          }
138          makeDataProperty(indicesArray, groupInfo.oldGroupNumber, indices);
139          if (groups && groupInfo.groupName !== undefined) {
140              makeDataProperty(groups, groupInfo.groupName, indices);
141          }
142      }
143      makeDataProperty(indicesArray, "groups", groups);
144      return indicesArray;
145  }
146  function makeDataProperty(result, key, value) {
147      const existingDesc = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(result, key);
148      if (existingDesc ? existingDesc.configurable : Object.isExtensible(result)) {
149          const newDesc = {
150              enumerable: existingDesc ? existingDesc.enumerable : true,
151              configurable: existingDesc ? existingDesc.configurable : true,
152              writable: true,
153              value
154          };
155          Object.defineProperty(result, key, newDesc);
156      }
157  }
158  let groupRenumbers;
159  let hasBackreferences = false;
160  let nodesContainingCapturingGroup = new Set();
161  let containsCapturingGroupStack = [];
162  let containsCapturingGroup = false;
163  let nextNewGroupNumber = 1;
164  let measurementGroupStack = [];
165  let measurementGroupsForGroup = new Map();
166  let newGroupNumberForGroup = new Map();
167  const handlers = {
168      init() {
169          hasBackreferences = false;
170          nodesContainingCapturingGroup.clear();
171          containsCapturingGroupStack.length = 0;
172          containsCapturingGroup = false;
173          nextNewGroupNumber = 1;
174          measurementGroupStack.length = 0;
175          measurementGroupsForGroup.clear();
176          newGroupNumberForGroup.clear();
177          groupRenumbers = [];
178      },
179      RegExp(path) {
180          regexp_tree_1.traverse(path.node, visitor);
181          if (nodesContainingCapturingGroup.size > 0) {
182              regexp_tree_1.transform(path.node, builder);
183              regexp_tree_1.transform(path.node, groupRenumberer);
184              if (hasBackreferences) {
185                  regexp_tree_1.transform(path.node, backreferenceRenumberer);
186              }
187          }
188          return false;
189      }
190  };
191  const nodeCallbacks = {
192      pre(path) {
193          containsCapturingGroupStack.push(containsCapturingGroup);
194          containsCapturingGroup = path.node.type === "Group" && path.node.capturing;
195      },
196      post(path) {
197          if (containsCapturingGroup) {
198              nodesContainingCapturingGroup.add(path.node);
199          }
200          containsCapturingGroup = containsCapturingGroupStack.pop() || containsCapturingGroup;
201      }
202  };
203  const visitor = {
204      Alternative: nodeCallbacks,
205      Disjunction: nodeCallbacks,
206      Assertion: nodeCallbacks,
207      Group: nodeCallbacks,
208      Repetition: nodeCallbacks,
209      Backreference(path) { hasBackreferences = true; }
210  };
211  const builder = {
212      Alternative(path) {
213          if (nodesContainingCapturingGroup.has(path.node)) {
214              // aa(b)c       -> (aa)(b)c
215              // aa(b)c(d)    -> (aa)(b)(c)(d)
216              // aa(b)+c(d)   -> (aa)((b)+)(c)(d);
217              let lastMeasurementIndex = 0;
218              let pendingTerms = [];
219              const measurementGroups = [];
220              const terms = [];
221              for (let i = 0; i < path.node.expressions.length; i++) {
222                  const term = path.node.expressions[i];
223                  if (nodesContainingCapturingGroup.has(term)) {
224                      if (i > lastMeasurementIndex) {
225                          const measurementGroup = {
226                              type: "Group",
227                              capturing: true,
228                              number: -1,
229                              expression: pendingTerms.length > 1 ? { type: "Alternative", expressions: pendingTerms } :
230                                  pendingTerms.length === 1 ? pendingTerms[0] :
231                                      null
232                          };
233                          terms.push(measurementGroup);
234                          measurementGroups.push(measurementGroup);
235                          lastMeasurementIndex = i;
236                          pendingTerms = [];
237                      }
238                      measurementGroupStack.push(measurementGroups);
239                      regexp_tree_1.transform(term, builder);
240                      measurementGroupStack.pop();
241                      pendingTerms.push(term);
242                      continue;
243                  }
244                  pendingTerms.push(term);
245              }
246              path.update({ expressions: terms.concat(pendingTerms) });
247          }
248          return false;
249      },
250      Group(path) {
251          if (!path.node.capturing)
252              return;
253          measurementGroupsForGroup.set(path.node, getMeasurementGroups());
254      }
255  };
256  const groupRenumberer = {
257      Group(path) {
258          if (!groupRenumbers)
259              throw new Error("Not initialized.");
260          if (!path.node.capturing)
261              return;
262          const oldGroupNumber = path.node.number;
263          const newGroupNumber = nextNewGroupNumber++;
264          const measurementGroups = measurementGroupsForGroup.get(path.node);
265          if (oldGroupNumber !== -1) {
266              groupRenumbers.push({
267                  oldGroupNumber,
268                  newGroupNumber,
269                  measurementGroups: measurementGroups && measurementGroups.map(group => group.number),
270                  groupName: path.node.name
271              });
272              newGroupNumberForGroup.set(oldGroupNumber, newGroupNumber);
273          }
274          path.update({ number: newGroupNumber });
275      }
276  };
277  const backreferenceRenumberer = {
278      Backreference(path) {
279          const newGroupNumber = newGroupNumberForGroup.get(path.node.number);
280          if (newGroupNumber) {
281              if (path.node.kind === "number") {
282                  path.update({
283                      number: newGroupNumber,
284                      reference: newGroupNumber
285                  });
286              }
287              else {
288                  path.update({
289                      number: newGroupNumber
290                  });
291              }
292          }
293      }
294  };
295  function getMeasurementGroups() {
296      const measurementGroups = [];
297      for (const array of measurementGroupStack) {
298          for (const item of array) {
299              measurementGroups.push(item);
300          }
301      }
302      return measurementGroups;
303  }
304  function transformMeasurementGroups(ast) {
305      const result = regexp_tree_1.transform(ast, handlers);
306      return new regexp_tree_1.TransformResult(result.getAST(), groupRenumbers);
307  }
308  module.exports = exec;

464  var compatTransforms = __webpack_require__(24845);
465  var _transform = __webpack_require__(42113);
466  
467  module.exports = {
468    /**
469     * Translates a regexp in new syntax to equivalent regexp in old syntax.
470     *
471     * @param string|RegExp|AST - regexp
472     * @param Array transformsWhitelist - names of the transforms to apply
473     */
474    transform: function transform(regexp) {
475      var transformsWhitelist = arguments.length > 1 && arguments[1] !== undefined ? arguments[1] : [];
476  
477      var transformToApply = transformsWhitelist.length > 0 ? transformsWhitelist : Object.keys(compatTransforms);
478  
479      var result = void 0;
480  
481      // Collect extra data per transform.
482      var extra = {};
483  
484      transformToApply.forEach(function (transformName) {
485  
486        if (!compatTransforms.hasOwnProperty(transformName)) {
487          throw new Error('Unknown compat-transform: ' + transformName + '. ' + 'Available transforms are: ' + Object.keys(compatTransforms).join(', '));
488        }
489  
490        var handler = compatTransforms[transformName];
491  
492        result = _transform.transform(regexp, handler);
493        regexp = result.getAST();
494  
495        // Collect `extra` transform result.
496        if (typeof handler.getExtra === 'function') {
497          extra[transformName] = handler.getExtra();
498        }
499      });
500  
501      // Set the final extras for all transforms.
502      result.setExtra(extra);
503  
504      return result;
505    }
506  };

523   *
524   * E.g. it tracks names of the capturing groups, in order to access the

530  var _createClass = function () { function defineProperties(target, props) { for (var i = 0; i < props.length; i++) { var descriptor = props[i]; descriptor.enumerable = descriptor.enumerable || false; descriptor.configurable = true; if ("value" in descriptor) descriptor.writable = true; Object.defineProperty(target, descriptor.key, descriptor); } } return function (Constructor, protoProps, staticProps) { if (protoProps) defineProperties(Constructor.prototype, protoProps); if (staticProps) defineProperties(Constructor, staticProps); return Constructor; }; }();

532  function _classCallCheck(instance, Constructor) { if (!(instance instanceof Constructor)) { throw new TypeError("Cannot call a class as a function"); } }

534  var RegExpTree = function () {
535    /**
536     * Initializes a `RegExpTree` instance.
537     *
538     * @param RegExp - a regular expression
539     *
540     * @param Object state:

542     *   An extra state which may store any related to transformation
543     *   data, for example, names of the groups.
544     *
545     *   - flags - original flags
546     *   - groups - names of the groups, and their indices
547     *   - source - original source
548     */
549    function RegExpTree(re, _ref) {
550      var flags = _ref.flags,
551          groups = _ref.groups,
552          source = _ref.source;
553  
554      _classCallCheck(this, RegExpTree);
555  
556      this._re = re;
557      this._groups = groups;

560      this.flags = flags;
561      this.source = source || re.source;
562      this.dotAll = flags.includes('s');
563  
564      // Inherited directly from `re`.
565      this.global = re.global;
566      this.ignoreCase = re.ignoreCase;
567      this.multiline = re.multiline;
568      this.sticky = re.sticky;

580        return this._re.test(string);

600        if (!this._toStringResult) {

608       */

612      value: function exec(string) {
613        var result = this._re.exec(string);

649  /**
650   * A regexp-tree plugin to translate `/./s` to `/[\0-\uFFFF]/`.
651   */
652  
653  module.exports = {
654  
655    // Whether `u` flag present. In which case we transform to
656    // \u{10FFFF} instead of \uFFFF.
657    _hasUFlag: false,
658  
659    // Only run this plugin if we have `s` flag.
660    shouldRun: function shouldRun(ast) {
661      var shouldRun = ast.flags.includes('s');
662  
663      if (!shouldRun) {
664        return false;
665      }
666  
667      // Strip the `s` flag.
668      ast.flags = ast.flags.replace('s', '');
669  
670      // Whether we have also `u`.
671      this._hasUFlag = ast.flags.includes('u');
672  
673      return true;
674    },
675    Char: function Char(path) {
676      var node = path.node;
677  
678  
679      if (node.kind !== 'meta' || node.value !== '.') {
680        return;
681      }
682  
683      var toValue = '\\uFFFF';
684      var toSymbol = '\uFFFF';
685  
686      if (this._hasUFlag) {
687        toValue = '\\u{10FFFF}';
688        toSymbol = '\uDBFF\uDFFF';
689      }
690  
691      path.replace({
692        type: 'CharacterClass',
693        expressions: [{
694          type: 'ClassRange',
695          from: {
696            type: 'Char',
697            value: '\\0',
698            kind: 'decimal',
699            symbol: '\0'
700          },
701          to: {
702            type: 'Char',
703            value: toValue,
704            kind: 'unicode',
705            symbol: toSymbol
706          }
707        }]
708      });
709    }
710  };

841  /**
842   * Helper `gen` function calls node type handler.
843   */
844  
845  function gen(node) {
846    return node ? generator[node.type](node) : '';
847  }
848  
849  /**
850   * AST handler.
851   */
852  var generator = {
853    RegExp: function RegExp(node) {
854      return '/' + gen(node.body) + '/' + node.flags;
855    },
856    Alternative: function Alternative(node) {
857      return (node.expressions || []).map(gen).join('');
858    },
859    Disjunction: function Disjunction(node) {
860      return gen(node.left) + '|' + gen(node.right);
861    },
862    Group: function Group(node) {
863      var expression = gen(node.expression);
864  
865      if (node.capturing) {
866        // A named group.
867        if (node.name) {
868          return '(?<' + (node.nameRaw || node.name) + '>' + expression + ')';
869        }
870  
871        return '(' + expression + ')';
872      }
873  
874      return '(?:' + expression + ')';
875    },
876    Backreference: function Backreference(node) {
877      switch (node.kind) {
878        case 'number':
879          return '\\' + node.reference;
880        case 'name':
881          return '\\k<' + (node.referenceRaw || node.reference) + '>';
882        default:
883          throw new TypeError('Unknown Backreference kind: ' + node.kind);
884      }
885    },
886    Assertion: function Assertion(node) {
887      switch (node.kind) {
888        case '^':
889        case '$':
890        case '\\b':
891        case '\\B':
892          return node.kind;
893  
894        case 'Lookahead':
895          {
896            var assertion = gen(node.assertion);
897  
898            if (node.negative) {
899              return '(?!' + assertion + ')';
900            }
901  
902            return '(?=' + assertion + ')';
903          }
904  
905        case 'Lookbehind':
906          {
907            var _assertion = gen(node.assertion);
908  
909            if (node.negative) {
910              return '(?<!' + _assertion + ')';
911            }
912  
913            return '(?<=' + _assertion + ')';
914          }
915  
916        default:
917          throw new TypeError('Unknown Assertion kind: ' + node.kind);
918      }
919    },
920    CharacterClass: function CharacterClass(node) {
921      var expressions = node.expressions.map(gen).join('');
922  
923      if (node.negative) {
924        return '[^' + expressions + ']';
925      }
926  
927      return '[' + expressions + ']';
928    },
929    ClassRange: function ClassRange(node) {
930      return gen(node.from) + '-' + gen(node.to);
931    },
932    Repetition: function Repetition(node) {
933      return '' + gen(node.expression) + gen(node.quantifier);
934    },
935    Quantifier: function Quantifier(node) {
936      var quantifier = void 0;
937      var greedy = node.greedy ? '' : '?';
938  
939      switch (node.kind) {
940        case '+':
941        case '?':
942        case '*':
943          quantifier = node.kind;
944          break;
945        case 'Range':
946          // Exact: {1}
947          if (node.from === node.to) {
948            quantifier = '{' + node.from + '}';
949          }
950          // Open: {1,}
951          else if (!node.to) {
952              quantifier = '{' + node.from + ',}';
953            }
954            // Closed: {1,3}
955            else {
956                quantifier = '{' + node.from + ',' + node.to + '}';
957              }
958          break;
959        default:
960          throw new TypeError('Unknown Quantifier kind: ' + node.kind);
961      }
962  
963      return '' + quantifier + greedy;
964    },
965    Char: function Char(node) {
966      var value = node.value;
967  
968      switch (node.kind) {
969        case 'simple':
970          {
971            if (node.escaped) {
972              return '\\' + value;
973            }
974            return value;
975          }
976  
977        case 'hex':
978        case 'unicode':
979        case 'oct':
980        case 'decimal':
981        case 'control':
982        case 'meta':
983          return value;
984  
985        default:
986          throw new TypeError('Unknown Char kind: ' + node.kind);
987      }
988    },
989    UnicodeProperty: function UnicodeProperty(node) {
990      var escapeChar = node.negative ? 'P' : 'p';
991      var namePart = void 0;
992  
993      if (!node.shorthand && !node.binary) {
994        namePart = node.name + '=';
995      } else {
996        namePart = '';
997      }
998  
999      return '\\' + escapeChar + '{' + namePart + node.value + '}';
1000   }
1001 };

1406 /**
1407  * Checks whether states go to the same set.
1408  */
1409 function goToSameSet(s1, s2, table, symbol) {
1410   if (!currentTransitionMap[s1] || !currentTransitionMap[s2]) {
1411     return false;
1412   }
1413 
1414   var originalTransitionS1 = table[s1][symbol];
1415   var originalTransitionS2 = table[s2][symbol];

1418   if (!originalTransitionS1 && !originalTransitionS2) {
1419     return true;
1420   }
1421

1423   return currentTransitionMap[s1].has(originalTransitionS1) && currentTransitionMap[s2].has(originalTransitionS2);

2057  */
2058 function repExplicit(fragment) {

2060   var outState = new NFAState({

2075 /**

2079 function rep(fragment) {
2080   fragment.in.addTransition(EPSILON, fragment.out);
2081   fragment.out.addTransition(EPSILON, fragment.in);

2089 function plusRep(fragment) {

2096  * the input to the output.

2098 function questionRep(fragment) {
2099   fragment.in.addTransition(EPSILON, fragment.out);

2812 module.exports = {
2813   /**
2814    * Optimizer transforms a regular expression into an optimized version,
2815    * replacing some sub-expressions with their idiomatic patterns.
2816    *
2817    * @param string | RegExp | AST - a regexp to optimize.
2818    *
2819    * @return TransformResult - an optimized regexp.
2820    *
2821    * Example:
2822    *
2823    *   /[a-zA-Z_0-9][a-zA-Z_0-9]*\e{1,}/
2824    *
2825    * Optimized to:
2826    *
2827    *   /\w+e+/
2828    */
2829   optimize: function optimize(regexp) {
2830     var _ref = arguments.length > 1 && arguments[1] !== undefined ? arguments[1] : {},
2831         _ref$whitelist = _ref.whitelist,
2832         whitelist = _ref$whitelist === undefined ? [] : _ref$whitelist,
2833         _ref$blacklist = _ref.blacklist,
2834         blacklist = _ref$blacklist === undefined ? [] : _ref$blacklist;
2835 
2836     var transformsRaw = whitelist.length > 0 ? whitelist : Array.from(optimizationTransforms.keys());
2837 
2838     var transformToApply = transformsRaw.filter(function (transform) {
2839       return !blacklist.includes(transform);
2840     });
2841 
2842     var ast = regexp;
2843     if (regexp instanceof RegExp) {
2844       regexp = '' + regexp;
2845     }
2846 
2847     if (typeof regexp === 'string') {
2848       ast = parser.parse(regexp);
2849     }
2850 
2851     var result = new transform.TransformResult(ast);
2852     var prevResultString = void 0;
2853 
2854     do {
2855       // Get a copy of the current state here so
2856       // we can compare it with the state at the
2857       // end of the loop.
2858       prevResultString = result.toString();
2859       ast = clone(result.getAST());
2860 
2861       transformToApply.forEach(function (transformName) {
2862         if (!optimizationTransforms.has(transformName)) {
2863           throw new Error('Unknown optimization-transform: ' + transformName + '. ' + 'Available transforms are: ' + Array.from(optimizationTransforms.keys()).join(', '));
2864         }
2865 
2866         var transformer = optimizationTransforms.get(transformName);
2867 
2868         // Don't override result just yet since we
2869         // might want to rollback the transform
2870         var newResult = transform.transform(ast, transformer);
2871 
2872         if (newResult.toString() !== result.toString()) {
2873           if (newResult.toString().length <= result.toString().length) {
2874             result = newResult;
2875           } else {
2876             // Result has changed but is not shorter:
2877             // restore ast to its previous state.
2878 
2879             ast = clone(result.getAST());
2880           }
2881         }
2882       });
2883 
2884       // Keep running the optimizer until it stops
2885       // making any change to the regexp.
2886     } while (result.toString() !== prevResultString);
2887 
2888     return result;
2889   }

2931     if (!this._hasUFlag && node.codePoint >= 0x1000) {
2932       return;
2933     }
2934 
2935     if (parent.type === 'ClassRange') {
2936       // The only class ranges we handle must be inside A-Z.
2937       // After the `from` char is processed, the isAZClassRange test
2938       // will be false, so we use a Set to keep track of parents and
2939       // process the `to` char.
2940       if (!this._AZClassRanges.has(parent) && !isAZClassRange(parent)) {
2941         return;
2942       }
2943       this._AZClassRanges.add(parent);
2944     }
2945 
2946     var lower = node.symbol.toLowerCase();
2947     if (lower !== node.symbol) {
2948       node.value = displaySymbolAsValue(lower, node);
2949       node.symbol = lower;
2950       node.codePoint = lower.codePointAt(0);
2951     }
2952   }
2953 };

2955 function isAZClassRange(classRange) {
2956   var from = classRange.from,
2957       to = classRange.to;
2958   // A-Z
2959 
2960   return from.codePoint >= UPPER_A_CP && from.codePoint <= UPPER_Z_CP && to.codePoint >= UPPER_A_CP && to.codePoint <= UPPER_Z_CP;

2963 function displaySymbolAsValue(symbol, node) {
2964   var codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
2965   if (node.kind === 'decimal') {
2966     return '\\' + codePoint;
2967   }
2968   if (node.kind === 'oct') {
2969     return '\\0' + codePoint.toString(8);
2970   }
2971   if (node.kind === 'hex') {
2972     return '\\x' + codePoint.toString(16);
2973   }
2974   if (node.kind === 'unicode') {
2975     if (node.isSurrogatePair) {
2976       var _getSurrogatePairFrom = getSurrogatePairFromCodePoint(codePoint),
2977           lead = _getSurrogatePairFrom.lead,
2978           trail = _getSurrogatePairFrom.trail;
2979 
2980       return '\\u' + '0'.repeat(4 - lead.length) + lead + '\\u' + '0'.repeat(4 - trail.length) + trail;
2981     } else if (node.value.includes('{')) {
2982       return '\\u{' + codePoint.toString(16) + '}';
2983     } else {
2984       var code = codePoint.toString(16);
2985       return '\\u' + '0'.repeat(4 - code.length) + code;
2986     }
2987   }
2988   // simple
2989   return symbol;

2992 /**

2994  * Conversion algorithm is taken from The Unicode Standard 3.0 Section 3.7
2995  * (https://www.unicode.org/versions/Unicode3.0.0/ch03.pdf)
2996  * @param {number} codePoint - Between 0x10000 and 0x10ffff
2997  * @returns {{lead: string, trail: string}}

2999 function getSurrogatePairFromCodePoint(codePoint) {
3000   var lead = Math.floor((codePoint - 0x10000) / 0x400) + 0xd800;
3001   var trail = (codePoint - 0x10000) % 0x400 + 0xdc00;
3002   return {
3003     lead: lead.toString(16),
3004     trail: trail.toString(16)
3005   };

3023  * [a-ec] -> [a-e]
3024  * [a-ec-e] -> [a-e]
3025  * [\w\da-f] -> [\w]
3026  * [abcdef] -> [a-f]

3031   init: function init(ast) {
3032     this._hasIUFlags = ast.flags.includes('i') && ast.flags.includes('u');
3033   },
3034   CharacterClass: function CharacterClass(path) {
3035     var node = path.node;
3036 
3037     var expressions = node.expressions;
3038 
3039     var metas = [];

3063 /**
3064  * Sorts expressions in char class in the following order:
3065  * - meta chars, ordered alphabetically by value
3066  * - chars (except `control` kind) and class ranges, ordered alphabetically (`from` char is used for class ranges)
3067  * - if ambiguous, class range comes before char
3068  * - if ambiguous between two class ranges, orders alphabetically by `to` char
3069  * - control chars, ordered alphabetically by value
3070  * @param {Object} a - Left Char or ClassRange node
3071  * @param {Object} b - Right Char or ClassRange node
3072  * @returns {number}
3073  */
3074 function sortCharClass(a, b) {
3075   var aValue = getSortValue(a);
3076   var bValue = getSortValue(b);
3077 
3078   if (aValue === bValue) {
3079     // We want ClassRange before Char
3080     // [bb-d] -> [b-db]
3081     if (a.type === 'ClassRange' && b.type !== 'ClassRange') {
3082       return -1;
3083     }
3084     if (b.type === 'ClassRange' && a.type !== 'ClassRange') {
3085       return 1;
3086     }
3087     if (a.type === 'ClassRange' && b.type === 'ClassRange') {
3088       return getSortValue(a.to) - getSortValue(b.to);
3089     }
3090     if (isMeta(a) && isMeta(b) || isControl(a) && isControl(b)) {
3091       return a.value < b.value ? -1 : 1;
3092     }
3093   }
3094   return aValue - bValue;
3095 }

3248 /**

3252  */
3253 function combinesWithPrecedingClassRange(expression, classRange) {
3254   if (classRange && classRange.type === 'ClassRange') {
3255     if (fitsInClassRange(expression, classRange)) {
3256       // [a-gc] -> [a-g]
3257       // [a-gc-e] -> [a-g]
3258       return true;
3259     } else if (
3260     // We only want \w chars or char codes to keep readability
3261     isMetaWCharOrCode(expression) && classRange.to.codePoint === expression.codePoint - 1) {
3262       // [a-de] -> [a-e]
3263       classRange.to = expression;
3264       return true;
3265     } else if (expression.type === 'ClassRange' && expression.from.codePoint <= classRange.to.codePoint + 1 && expression.to.codePoint >= classRange.from.codePoint - 1) {
3266       // [a-db-f] -> [a-f]
3267       // [b-fa-d] -> [a-f]
3268       // [a-cd-f] -> [a-f]
3269       if (expression.from.codePoint < classRange.from.codePoint) {
3270         classRange.from = expression.from;
3271       }
3272       if (expression.to.codePoint > classRange.to.codePoint) {
3273         classRange.to = expression.to;
3274       }
3275       return true;
3276     }
3277   }
3278   return false;

3913 function consumeNumbers(startIndex, parent, rtl) {
3914   var i = startIndex;
3915   var siblingNode = (rtl ? i >= 0 : i < parent.expressions.length) && parent.expressions[i];
3916

3929 function preservesOpeningCurlyBraceEscape(index, parent) {
3930   // (?:\{) -> (?:{)
3931   if (index == null) {
3932     return false;
3933   }
3934

3958   // (?:\{) -> (?:{)
3959   if (index == null) {
3960     return false;

3976

4441 /**
4442  * A regexp-tree plugin to replace different range-based quantifiers

4444  *

4446  * a{1,} -> a+

4450  *

4457 
4458

4488

4491     return;
4492   }
4493 
4494   node.kind = '+';
4495   delete node.from;

4524 /**
4525  * A regexp-tree plugin to merge quantifiers
4526  *
4527  * a+a+ -> a{2,}
4528  * a{2}a{3} -> a{5}
4529  * a{1,2}a{2,3} -> a{3,5}
4530  */
4531

4533 module.exports = {
4534   Repetition: function Repetition(path) {
4535     var node = path.node,
4536         parent = path.parent;
4537 
4538 
4539     if (parent.type !== 'Alternative' || !path.index) {
4540       return;
4541     }
4542 
4543     var previousSibling = path.getPreviousSibling();
4544 
4545     if (!previousSibling) {
4546       return;
4547     }
4548 
4549     if (previousSibling.node.type === 'Repetition') {
4550       if (!previousSibling.getChild().hasEqualSource(path.getChild())) {
4551         return;
4552       }
4553

4555           previousSiblingFrom = _extractFromTo.from,
4556           previousSiblingTo = _extractFromTo.to;
4557 
4558       var _extractFromTo2 = extractFromTo(node.quantifier),
4559           nodeFrom = _extractFromTo2.from,
4560           nodeTo = _extractFromTo2.to;

4562       // It's does not seem reliable to merge quantifiers with different greediness
4563       // when none of both is a greedy open range
4564

4567         return;

4571       // a*a+ -> a+
4572       // a+a+ -> a{2,}
4573       // a{2}a{4} -> a{6}
4574       // a{1,2}a{2,3} -> a{3,5}
4575       // a{1,}a{2,} -> a{3,}
4576       // a+a{2,} -> a{3,}
4577

4579       // a*?a{2,} -> a{2,}

4586       } else {
4587         delete node.quantifier.to;
4588       }

4591       }

4596         return;
4597       }
4598

4600       previousSibling.remove();
4601     }

4605 function isGreedyOpenRange(quantifier) {
4606   return quantifier.greedy && (quantifier.kind === '+' || quantifier.kind === '*' || quantifier.kind === 'Range' && !quantifier.to);

4609 function extractFromTo(quantifier) {

5716 /**
5717  * Extracts ranges from the range string.
5718  */
5719 function getRange(text) {
5720   var range = text.match(/\d+/g).map(Number);
5721 
5722   if (Number.isFinite(range[1]) && range[1] < range[0]) {
5723     throw new SyntaxError('Numbers out of order in ' + text + ' quantifier');
5724   }
5725 
5726   return range;
5727 }

5729 /**

5731  */
5732 function checkClassRange(from, to) {
5733   if (from.kind === 'control' || to.kind === 'control' || !isNaN(from.codePoint) && !isNaN(to.codePoint) && from.codePoint > to.codePoint) {
5734     throw new SyntaxError('Range ' + from.value + '-' + to.value + ' out of order in character class');
5735   }

5742 /**
5743  * Unicode property.
5744  */
5745 function UnicodeProperty(matched, loc) {
5746   var negative = matched[1] === 'P';
5747   var separatorIdx = matched.indexOf('=');
5748 
5749   var name = matched.slice(3, separatorIdx !== -1 ? separatorIdx : -1);
5750   var value = void 0;
5751 
5752   // General_Category allows using only value as a shorthand.
5753   var isShorthand = separatorIdx === -1 && unicodeProperties.isGeneralCategoryValue(name);
5754 
5755   // Binary propery name.
5756   var isBinaryProperty = separatorIdx === -1 && unicodeProperties.isBinaryPropertyName(name);
5757 
5758   if (isShorthand) {
5759     value = name;
5760     name = 'General_Category';
5761   } else if (isBinaryProperty) {
5762     value = name;
5763   } else {
5764     if (!unicodeProperties.isValidName(name)) {
5765       throw new SyntaxError('Invalid unicode property name: ' + name + '.');
5766     }
5767 
5768     value = matched.slice(separatorIdx + 1, -1);
5769 
5770     if (!unicodeProperties.isValidValue(name, value)) {
5771       throw new SyntaxError('Invalid ' + name + ' unicode property value: ' + value + '.');
5772     }
5773   }
5774 
5775   return Node({
5776     type: 'UnicodeProperty',
5777     name: name,
5778     value: value,
5779     negative: negative,
5780     shorthand: isShorthand,
5781     binary: isBinaryProperty,
5782     canonicalName: unicodeProperties.getCanonicalName(name) || name,
5783     canonicalValue: unicodeProperties.getCanonicalValue(value) || value
5784   }, loc);
5785 }

5790 /**
5791  * Creates a character node.
5792  */
5793 function Char(value, kind, loc) {
5794   var symbol = void 0;
5795   var codePoint = void 0;
5796 
5797   switch (kind) {
5798     case 'decimal':
5799       {
5800         codePoint = Number(value.slice(1));
5801         symbol = String.fromCodePoint(codePoint);
5802         break;
5803       }
5804     case 'oct':
5805       {
5806         codePoint = parseInt(value.slice(1), 8);
5807         symbol = String.fromCodePoint(codePoint);
5808         break;
5809       }
5810     case 'hex':
5811     case 'unicode':
5812       {
5813         if (value.lastIndexOf('\\u') > 0) {
5814           var _value$split$slice = value.split('\\u').slice(1),
5815               _value$split$slice2 = _slicedToArray(_value$split$slice, 2),
5816               lead = _value$split$slice2[0],
5817               trail = _value$split$slice2[1];
5818 
5819           lead = parseInt(lead, 16);
5820           trail = parseInt(trail, 16);
5821           codePoint = (lead - 0xd800) * 0x400 + (trail - 0xdc00) + 0x10000;
5822 
5823           symbol = String.fromCodePoint(codePoint);
5824         } else {
5825           var hex = value.slice(2).replace('{', '');
5826           codePoint = parseInt(hex, 16);
5827           if (codePoint > 0x10ffff) {
5828             throw new SyntaxError('Bad character escape sequence: ' + value);
5829           }
5830 
5831           symbol = String.fromCodePoint(codePoint);
5832         }
5833         break;
5834       }
5835     case 'meta':
5836       {
5837         switch (value) {
5838           case '\\t':
5839             symbol = '\t';
5840             codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
5841             break;
5842           case '\\n':
5843             symbol = '\n';
5844             codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
5845             break;
5846           case '\\r':
5847             symbol = '\r';
5848             codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
5849             break;
5850           case '\\v':
5851             symbol = '\v';
5852             codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
5853             break;
5854           case '\\f':
5855             symbol = '\f';
5856             codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
5857             break;
5858           case '\\b':
5859             symbol = '\b';
5860             codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
5861           case '\\0':
5862             symbol = '\0';
5863             codePoint = 0;
5864           case '.':
5865             symbol = '.';
5866             codePoint = NaN;
5867             break;
5868           default:
5869             codePoint = NaN;
5870         }
5871         break;
5872       }
5873     case 'simple':
5874       {
5875         symbol = value;
5876         codePoint = symbol.codePointAt(0);
5877         break;
5878       }
5879   }
5880 
5881   return Node({
5882     type: 'Char',
5883     value: value,
5884     kind: kind,
5885     symbol: symbol,
5886     codePoint: codePoint
5887   }, loc);
5888 }

5890 /**
5891  * Valid flags per current ECMAScript spec and
5892  * stage 3+ proposals.
5893  */
5894 var validFlags = 'gimsuxy';
5895 
5896 /**
5897  * Checks the flags are valid, and that
5898  * we don't duplicate flags.
5899  */
5900 function checkFlags(flags) {
5901   var seen = new Set();
5902 
5903   var _iteratorNormalCompletion = true;
5904   var _didIteratorError = false;
5905   var _iteratorError = undefined;
5906 
5907   try {

5909       var flag = _step.value;
5910 
5911       if (seen.has(flag) || !validFlags.includes(flag)) {
5912         throw new SyntaxError('Invalid flags: ' + flags);
5913       }
5914       seen.add(flag);
5915     }
5916   } catch (err) {
5917     _didIteratorError = true;
5918     _iteratorError = err;
5919   } finally {
5920     try {
5921       if (!_iteratorNormalCompletion && _iterator.return) {
5922         _iterator.return();
5923       }
5924     } finally {
5925       if (_didIteratorError) {
5926         throw _iteratorError;
5927       }
5928     }
5929   }
5930 
5931   return flags.split('').sort().join('');
5932 }
5933 
5934 /**
5935  * Parses patterns like \1, \2, etc. either as a backreference
5936  * to a group, or a deciaml char code.
5937  */
5938 function GroupRefOrDecChar(text, textLoc) {
5939   var reference = Number(text.slice(1));
5940 
5941   if (reference > 0 && reference <= capturingGroupsCount) {
5942     return Node({
5943       type: 'Backreference',
5944       kind: 'number',
5945       number: reference,
5946       reference: reference
5947     }, textLoc);
5948   }
5949 
5950   return Char(text, 'decimal', textLoc);
5951 }
5952 
5953 /**
5954  * Unicode names.
5955  */
5956 var uReStart = /^\\u[0-9a-fA-F]{4}/; // only matches start of string
5957 var ucpReStart = /^\\u\{[0-9a-fA-F]{1,}\}/; // only matches start of string
5958 var ucpReAnywhere = /\\u\{[0-9a-fA-F]{1,}\}/; // matches anywhere in string
5959 
5960 /**
5961  * Validates Unicode group name.
5962  */
5963 function validateUnicodeGroupName(name, state) {
5964   var isUnicodeName = ucpReAnywhere.test(name);
5965   var isUnicodeState = state === 'u' || state === 'xu' || state === 'u_class';
5966 
5967   if (isUnicodeName && !isUnicodeState) {
5968     throw new SyntaxError('invalid group Unicode name "' + name + '", use `u` flag.');
5969   }
5970 
5971   return name;
5972 }
5973 
5974 // Matches the following production: https://tc39.es/ecma262/#prod-RegExpUnicodeEscapeSequence
5975 //
5976 //  RegExpUnicodeEscapeSequence ::
5977 //    `u` LeadSurrogate `\u` TrailSurrogate   # as 'leadSurrogate', 'trailSurrogate'
5978 //    `u` LeadSurrogate                       # as 'leadSurrogateOnly'
5979 //    `u` TrailSurrogate                      # as 'trailSurrogateOnly'
5980 //    `u` NonSurrogate                        # as 'nonSurrogate'
5981 //    `u` `{` CodePoint `}`                   # as 'codePoint'
5982 //
5983 //  LeadSurrogate ::
5984 //    Hex4Digits but only if the SV of Hex4Digits is in the inclusive range 0xD800 to 0xDBFF        # [dD][89aAbB][0-9a-fA-F]{2}
5985 //
5986 //  TrailSurrogate ::
5987 //    Hex4Digits but only if the SV of Hex4Digits is in the inclusive range 0xDC00 to 0xDFFF        # [dD][c-fC-F][0-9a-fA-F]{2}
5988 //
5989 //  NonSurrogate ::
5990 //    Hex4Digits but only if the SV of Hex4Digits is not in the inclusive range 0xD800 to 0xDFFF    # [0-9a-ce-fA-CE-F][0-9a-fA-F]{3}|[dD][0-7][0-9a-fA-F]{2}
5991 //
5992 //  CodePoint ::
5993 //    HexDigits but only if MV of HexDigits ≤ 0x10FFFF                                              # 0*(?:[0-9a-fA-F]{1,5}|10[0-9a-fA-F]{4})
5994 //
5995 var uidRe = /\\u(?:([dD][89aAbB][0-9a-fA-F]{2})\\u([dD][c-fC-F][0-9a-fA-F]{2})|([dD][89aAbB][0-9a-fA-F]{2})|([dD][c-fC-F][0-9a-fA-F]{2})|([0-9a-ce-fA-CE-F][0-9a-fA-F]{3}|[dD][0-7][0-9a-fA-F]{2})|\{(0*(?:[0-9a-fA-F]{1,5}|10[0-9a-fA-F]{4}))\})/;
5996 
5997 function decodeUnicodeGroupName(name) {
5998   return name.replace(new RegExp(uidRe, 'g'), function (_, leadSurrogate, trailSurrogate, leadSurrogateOnly, trailSurrogateOnly, nonSurrogate, codePoint) {
5999     if (leadSurrogate) {
6000       return String.fromCodePoint(parseInt(leadSurrogate, 16), parseInt(trailSurrogate, 16));
6001     }
6002     if (leadSurrogateOnly) {
6003       return String.fromCodePoint(parseInt(leadSurrogateOnly, 16));
6004     }
6005     if (trailSurrogateOnly) {
6006       // TODO: Per the spec: https://tc39.es/ecma262/#prod-RegExpUnicodeEscapeSequence
6007       // > Each `\u` TrailSurrogate for which the choice of associated `u` LeadSurrogate is ambiguous shall be associated with the nearest possible `u` LeadSurrogate that would otherwise have no corresponding `\u` TrailSurrogate.
6008       return String.fromCodePoint(parseInt(trailSurrogateOnly, 16));
6009     }
6010     if (nonSurrogate) {
6011       return String.fromCodePoint(parseInt(nonSurrogate, 16));
6012     }
6013     if (codePoint) {
6014       return String.fromCodePoint(parseInt(codePoint, 16));
6015     }
6016     return _;
6017   });
6018 }
6019 
6020 /**
6021  * Extracts from `\k<foo>` pattern either a backreference
6022  * to a named capturing group (if it presents), or parses it
6023  * as a list of char: `\k`, `<`, `f`, etc.
6024  */
6025 function NamedGroupRefOrChars(text, textLoc) {
6026   var referenceRaw = text.slice(3, -1);
6027   var reference = decodeUnicodeGroupName(referenceRaw);
6028 
6029   if (namedGroups.hasOwnProperty(reference)) {
6030     return Node({
6031       type: 'Backreference',
6032       kind: 'name',
6033       number: namedGroups[reference],
6034       reference: reference,
6035       referenceRaw: referenceRaw
6036     }, textLoc);
6037   }
6038 
6039   // Else `\k<foo>` should be parsed as a list of `Char`s.
6040   // This is really a 0.01% edge case, but we should handle it.
6041 
6042   var startOffset = null;
6043   var startLine = null;
6044   var endLine = null;
6045   var startColumn = null;
6046 
6047   if (textLoc) {
6048     startOffset = textLoc.startOffset;
6049     startLine = textLoc.startLine;
6050     endLine = textLoc.endLine;
6051     startColumn = textLoc.startColumn;
6052   }
6053 
6054   var charRe = /^[\w$<>]/;
6055   var loc = void 0;
6056 
6057   var chars = [
6058   // Init to first \k, taking 2 symbols.
6059   Char(text.slice(1, 2), 'simple', startOffset ? {
6060     startLine: startLine,
6061     endLine: endLine,
6062     startColumn: startColumn,
6063     startOffset: startOffset,
6064     endOffset: startOffset += 2,
6065     endColumn: startColumn += 2
6066   } : null)];
6067 
6068   // For \k
6069   chars[0].escaped = true;
6070 
6071   // Other symbols.
6072   text = text.slice(2);
6073 
6074   while (text.length > 0) {
6075     var matched = null;
6076 
6077     // Unicode, \u003B or \u{003B}
6078     if ((matched = text.match(uReStart)) || (matched = text.match(ucpReStart))) {
6079       if (startOffset) {
6080         loc = {
6081           startLine: startLine,
6082           endLine: endLine,
6083           startColumn: startColumn,
6084           startOffset: startOffset,
6085           endOffset: startOffset += matched[0].length,
6086           endColumn: startColumn += matched[0].length
6087         };
6088       }
6089       chars.push(Char(matched[0], 'unicode', loc));
6090       text = text.slice(matched[0].length);
6091     }
6092 
6093     // Simple char.
6094     else if (matched = text.match(charRe)) {
6095         if (startOffset) {
6096           loc = {
6097             startLine: startLine,
6098             endLine: endLine,
6099             startColumn: startColumn,
6100             startOffset: startOffset,
6101             endOffset: ++startOffset,
6102             endColumn: ++startColumn
6103           };
6104         }
6105         chars.push(Char(matched[0], 'simple', loc));
6106         text = text.slice(1);
6107       }
6108   }
6109 
6110   return chars;
6111 }
6112 
6113 /**
6114  * Creates an AST node with a location.
6115  */
6116 function Node(node, loc) {
6117   if (yy.options.captureLocations) {
6118     node.loc = {
6119       source: parsingString.slice(loc.startOffset, loc.endOffset),
6120       start: {
6121         line: loc.startLine,
6122         column: loc.startColumn,
6123         offset: loc.startOffset
6124       },
6125       end: {
6126         line: loc.endLine,
6127         column: loc.endColumn,
6128         offset: loc.endOffset
6129       }
6130     };
6131   }
6132   return node;
6133 }
6134 
6135 /**
6136  * Creates location node.
6137  */
6138 function loc(start, end) {
6139   if (!yy.options.captureLocations) {
6140     return null;
6141   }
6142 
6143   return {
6144     startOffset: start.startOffset,
6145     endOffset: end.endOffset,
6146     startLine: start.startLine,
6147     endLine: end.endLine,
6148     startColumn: start.startColumn,
6149     endColumn: end.endColumn
6150   };
6151 }
6152 
6153 function unexpectedToken(token) {
6154   if (token.type === EOF) {
6155     unexpectedEndOfInput();
6156   }
6157 
6158   tokenizer.throwUnexpectedToken(token.value, token.startLine, token.startColumn);
6159 }
6160 
6161 function unexpectedEndOfInput() {
6162   parseError('Unexpected end of input.');
6163 }
6164 
6165 function parseError(message) {
6166   throw new SyntaxError(message);
6167 }

6479 function inverseMap(data) {
6480   var inverse = {};
6481 
6482   for (var name in data) {
6483     if (!data.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
6484       continue;
6485     }
6486     var value = data[name];
6487     if (Array.isArray(value)) {
6488       for (var i = 0; i < value.length; i++) {
6489         inverse[value[i]] = name;
6490       }
6491     } else {
6492       inverse[value] = name;
6493     }
6494   }
6495 
6496   return inverse;
6497 }

6501 }

6933 /**
6934  * Flattens a nested disjunction node to a list.
6935  *
6936  * /a|b|c|d/
6937  *
6938  * {{{a, b}, c}, d} -> [a, b, c, d]
6939  */
6940 
6941 function _toConsumableArray(arr) { if (Array.isArray(arr)) { for (var i = 0, arr2 = Array(arr.length); i < arr.length; i++) { arr2[i] = arr[i]; } return arr2; } else { return Array.from(arr); } }
6942 
6943 function disjunctionToList(node) {
6944   if (node.type !== 'Disjunction') {
6945     throw new TypeError('Expected "Disjunction" node, got "' + node.type + '"');
6946   }
6947 
6948   var list = [];
6949 
6950   if (node.left && node.left.type === 'Disjunction') {
6951     list.push.apply(list, _toConsumableArray(disjunctionToList(node.left)).concat([node.right]));
6952   } else {
6953     list.push(node.left, node.right);
6954   }
6955 
6956   return list;
6957 }
6958 
6959 /**
6960  * Builds a nested disjunction node from a list.
6961  *
6962  * /a|b|c|d/
6963  *
6964  * [a, b, c, d] -> {{{a, b}, c}, d}
6965  */
6966 function listToDisjunction(list) {
6967   return list.reduce(function (left, right) {
6968     return {
6969       type: 'Disjunction',
6970       left: left,
6971       right: right
6972     };
6973   });
6974 }

6976 /**
6977  * Increases a quantifier by one.
6978  * Does not change greediness.
6979  * * -> +
6980  * + -> {2,}
6981  * ? -> {1,2}
6982  * {2} -> {3}
6983  * {2,} -> {3,}
6984  * {2,3} -> {3,4}
6985  */
6986 function increaseQuantifierByOne(quantifier) {
6987   if (quantifier.kind === '*') {
6988 
6989     quantifier.kind = '+';
6990   } else if (quantifier.kind === '+') {
6991 
6992     quantifier.kind = 'Range';
6993     quantifier.from = 2;
6994     delete quantifier.to;
6995   } else if (quantifier.kind === '?') {
6996 
6997     quantifier.kind = 'Range';
6998     quantifier.from = 1;
6999     quantifier.to = 2;
7000   } else if (quantifier.kind === 'Range') {
7001 
7002     quantifier.from += 1;
7003     if (quantifier.to) {
7004       quantifier.to += 1;
7005     }
7006   }
7007 }

7011   listToDisjunction: listToDisjunction,
7012   increaseQuantifierByOne: increaseQuantifierByOne

7027 var NodePath = __webpack_require__(53636);
7028 
7029 /**
7030  * Does an actual AST traversal, using visitor pattern,
7031  * and calling set of callbacks.
7032  *
7033  * Based on https://github.com/olov/ast-traverse
7034  *
7035  * Expects AST in Mozilla Parser API: nodes which are supposed to be
7036  * handled should have `type` property.
7037  *
7038  * @param Object root - a root node to start traversal from.
7039  *
7040  * @param Object options - an object with set of callbacks:
7041  *
7042  *   - `pre(node, parent, prop, index)` - a hook called on node enter
7043  *   - `post`(node, parent, prop, index) - a hook called on node exit
7044  *   - `skipProperty(prop)` - a predicated whether a property should be skipped
7045  */
7046 function astTraverse(root) {
7047   var options = arguments.length > 1 && arguments[1] !== undefined ? arguments[1] : {};
7048 
7049   var pre = options.pre;
7050   var post = options.post;
7051   var skipProperty = options.skipProperty;
7052 
7053   function visit(node, parent, prop, idx) {
7054     if (!node || typeof node.type !== 'string') {
7055       return;
7056     }
7057 
7058     var res = undefined;
7059     if (pre) {
7060       res = pre(node, parent, prop, idx);
7061     }
7062 
7063     if (res !== false) {
7064 
7065       // A node can be replaced during traversal, so we have to
7066       // recalculate it from the parent, to avoid traversing "dead" nodes.
7067       if (parent && parent[prop]) {
7068         if (!isNaN(idx)) {
7069           node = parent[prop][idx];
7070         } else {
7071           node = parent[prop];
7072         }
7073       }
7074 
7075       for (var _prop in node) {
7076         if (node.hasOwnProperty(_prop)) {
7077           if (skipProperty ? skipProperty(_prop, node) : _prop[0] === '$') {
7078             continue;
7079           }
7080 
7081           var child = node[_prop];
7082 
7083           // Collection node.
7084           //
7085           // NOTE: a node (or several nodes) can be removed or inserted
7086           // during traversal.
7087           //
7088           // Current traversing index is stored on top of the
7089           // `NodePath.traversingIndexStack`. The stack is used to support
7090           // recursive nature of the traversal.
7091           //
7092           // In this case `NodePath.traversingIndex` (which we use here) is
7093           // updated in the NodePath remove/insert methods.
7094           //
7095           if (Array.isArray(child)) {
7096             var index = 0;
7097             NodePath.traversingIndexStack.push(index);
7098             while (index < child.length) {
7099               visit(child[index], node, _prop, index);
7100               index = NodePath.updateTraversingIndex(+1);
7101             }
7102             NodePath.traversingIndexStack.pop();
7103           }
7104 
7105           // Simple node.
7106           else {
7107               visit(child, node, _prop);
7108             }
7109         }
7110       }
7111     }
7112 
7113     if (post) {
7114       post(node, parent, prop, idx);
7115     }
7116   }
7117 
7118   visit(root, null);
7119 }
7120 
7121 module.exports = {
7122   /**
7123    * Traverses an AST.
7124    *
7125    * @param Object ast - an AST node
7126    *
7127    * @param Object | Array<Object> handlers:
7128    *
7129    *   an object (or an array of objects)
7130    *
7131    *   Each such object contains a handler function per node.
7132    *   In case of an array of handlers, they are applied in order.
7133    *   A handler may return a transformed node (or a different type).
7134    *
7135    *   The per-node function may instead be an object with functions pre and post.
7136    *   pre is called before visiting the node, post after.
7137    *   If a handler is a function, it is treated as the pre function, with an empty post.
7138    *
7139    * @param Object options:
7140    *
7141    *   a config object, specifying traversal options:
7142    *
7143    *   `asNodes`: boolean - whether handlers should receives raw AST nodes
7144    *   (false by default), instead of a `NodePath` wrapper. Note, by default
7145    *   `NodePath` wrapper provides a set of convenient method to manipulate
7146    *   a traversing AST, and also has access to all parents list. A raw
7147    *   nodes traversal should be used in rare cases, when no `NodePath`
7148    *   features are needed.
7149    *
7150    * Special hooks:
7151    *
7152    *   - `shouldRun(ast)` - a predicate determining whether the handler
7153    *                        should be applied.
7154    *
7155    * NOTE: Multiple handlers are used as an optimization of applying all of
7156    * them in one AST traversal pass.
7157    */
7158   traverse: function traverse(ast, handlers) {
7159     var options = arguments.length > 2 && arguments[2] !== undefined ? arguments[2] : { asNodes: false };
7160 
7161 
7162     if (!Array.isArray(handlers)) {
7163       handlers = [handlers];
7164     }
7165 
7166     // Filter out handlers by result of `shouldRun`, if the method is present.
7167     handlers = handlers.filter(function (handler) {
7168       if (typeof handler.shouldRun !== 'function') {
7169         return true;
7170       }
7171       return handler.shouldRun(ast);
7172     });
7173 
7174     NodePath.initRegistry();
7175 
7176     // Allow handlers to initializer themselves.
7177     handlers.forEach(function (handler) {
7178       if (typeof handler.init === 'function') {
7179         handler.init(ast);
7180       }
7181     });
7182 
7183     function getPathFor(node, parent, prop, index) {
7184       var parentPath = NodePath.getForNode(parent);
7185       var nodePath = NodePath.getForNode(node, parentPath, prop, index);
7186 
7187       return nodePath;
7188     }
7189 
7190     // Handle actual nodes.
7191     astTraverse(ast, {
7192       /**
7193        * Handler on node enter.
7194        */
7195       pre: function pre(node, parent, prop, index) {
7196         var nodePath = void 0;
7197         if (!options.asNodes) {
7198           nodePath = getPathFor(node, parent, prop, index);
7199         }
7200 
7201         var _iteratorNormalCompletion = true;
7202         var _didIteratorError = false;
7203         var _iteratorError = undefined;
7204 
7205         try {
7206           for (var _iterator = handlers[Symbol.iterator](), _step; !(_iteratorNormalCompletion = (_step = _iterator.next()).done); _iteratorNormalCompletion = true) {
7207             var handler = _step.value;
7208 
7209             // "Catch-all" `*` handler.
7210             if (typeof handler['*'] === 'function') {
7211               if (nodePath) {
7212                 // A path/node can be removed by some previous handler.
7213                 if (!nodePath.isRemoved()) {
7214                   var handlerResult = handler['*'](nodePath);
7215                   // Explicitly stop traversal.
7216                   if (handlerResult === false) {
7217                     return false;
7218                   }
7219                 }
7220               } else {
7221                 handler['*'](node, parent, prop, index);
7222               }
7223             }
7224 
7225             // Per-node handler.
7226             var handlerFuncPre = void 0;
7227             if (typeof handler[node.type] === 'function') {
7228               handlerFuncPre = handler[node.type];
7229             } else if (typeof handler[node.type] === 'object' && typeof handler[node.type].pre === 'function') {
7230               handlerFuncPre = handler[node.type].pre;
7231             }
7232 
7233             if (handlerFuncPre) {
7234               if (nodePath) {
7235                 // A path/node can be removed by some previous handler.
7236                 if (!nodePath.isRemoved()) {
7237                   var _handlerResult = handlerFuncPre.call(handler, nodePath);
7238                   // Explicitly stop traversal.
7239                   if (_handlerResult === false) {
7240                     return false;
7241                   }
7242                 }
7243               } else {
7244                 handlerFuncPre.call(handler, node, parent, prop, index);
7245               }
7246             }
7247           } // Loop over handlers
7248         } catch (err) {
7249           _didIteratorError = true;
7250           _iteratorError = err;

7778 /**
7779  * Performs a deep copy of an simple object.
7780  * Only handles scalar values, arrays and objects.
7781  *
7782  * @param obj Object
7783  */
7784 
7785 module.exports = function clone(obj) {
7786   if (obj === null || typeof obj !== 'object') {
7787     return obj;
7788   }
7789   var res = void 0;
7790   if (Array.isArray(obj)) {
7791     res = [];
7792   } else {
7793     res = {};
7794   }
7795   for (var i in obj) {
7796     res[i] = clone(obj[i]);
7797   }
7798   return res;
7799 };
